Ethical issues:
Ownership & Credit – Sharing someone else’s recipe without permission or proper credit

Cultural Appropriation – Taking traditional or cultural recipes and presenting them as your own

Commercial Misuse – Using a shared recipe for profit when it was intended for personal use only

Plagiarism – Copying a recipe and claiming authorship with minimal or no changes

Consent – Sharing recipes that were given privately, not meant for wider distribution

Food Safety Responsibility – Sharing unsafe, untested, or misleading instructions

Allergen Transparency – Failing to disclose allergens or dietary risks

Power Dynamics – Pressure to share “secret” or family recipes unwillingly

Equity & Access – Recipes assuming access to costly or rare ingredients, excluding others

Misrepresentation – Altering a recipe but still attributing it to the original creator
